The '''RF1 Driver Programme''', formerly known as '''Renault Driver Development''', is a program to support [[Auto racing|racing drivers]] since 2002 in their racing series. The programme was created by [[Renault in Formula One#Renault F1 Team <U+2013> (2002<U+2013>2010)|Renault F1]] in 2002.

Selected drivers have to prove their potential on track and their athletics qualities. They promote [[Renault]] in the world.

In 2011, the programme was renamed '''LRGP Academy''', following the rebranding of the team to "[[Renault_in_Formula_One#Lotus_Renault_GP_.282011.29|Lotus Renault GP]]".<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.formula1.com/news/headlines/2011/1/11650.html|date=19 January 2011|accessdate=19 January 2011|work=formula1.com|publisher=[[Formula One Group|Formula One Administration]]|title=Fairuz Fauzy to become Renault reserve}}</ref>

In 2012, the programme was renamed '''[[Lotus F1|Lotus F1 Team]] iRace Professional Programme'''.

